article_title: Obamacare Sticker Shock? Unlikely For Most In 2015

article_metadata.description: As health plans begin next month to submit their 2015 rate increases for Americans buying private coverage under the Affordable Care Act, it’s unlikely most of these individuals will have sticker shock, several reports and statements from health insurance executives indicate.
